{
  "stem": "13817.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I went into their house, and was thinking I was safe there because there was just this one woman-- two women.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after a while the Gestapo came there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And again I was hiding behind the door.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And behind the-- behind that door there was a water tank, and I was squeezed behind the water tank.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And again, they didn't find me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then two days later, the chief of police called my mother and said, let the boys come home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The arrest warrants are over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that was why we weren't at that time, neither my brothers or myself, arrested to go to the camps.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Well, this was the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And naturally after that, there came all the new laws out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Jews couldn't have any more of their businesses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Going back to Kristallnacht, a thousand excuses from the Nazis why they did it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was a young Jewish man whose parents were stranded between Germany and Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "His name was Grynszpan.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He went to the embassy in, in, in Paris and shot some third consul there, [NON-ENGLISH] employee.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this is what the Nazis used as a-- as an excuse to start the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But to came back in the spring or early summer of '38, already every Jew had to declare how much his property he had.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Everybody who had more than-- his property was worth more than 5,000 marks had to declare already his bank book and everything what they owed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then af-- during-- after the Kristallnacht, they put a so-called Juden tax on all the Jews who had more than 5,000 marks.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were already preparing for that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everybody had said the Jews were in fault for the Kristallnacht when everybody-- [DRINKS] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
